profile_positions.description:
•	Developed design documentation including design reports, technical specifications, drawings, BOQ’s and cost estimates for bridges, and road drainages for Volcano Community Resilience Project (VCRP), valued at $100 million; 
•	Contributed on Volcano Project proposal's technical reports targeting Green Climate Fund (GCF) and Adaptation Fund (AF);
•	Coordinated the planning and implementation of flood mitigation measures project Phase 3 in volcano region, with a budget of $1.2 million;
•	Successfully coordinated the implementation of flood control infrastructure projects Phases 1 &2 including bridges, retention ponds, lined and unlined open channel drainages in Volcano region;
•	Participated in Muvumba Multi-Purpose Dam project development as Project Engineer and sponsored by AfDB, including project gate document preparation, CDP preparation, FEED support to figure out technical issues and providing rough investment cost;
•	Lead the development of Flood Hazards maps and control the flow of storm and surface water, deliver effective civil engineering projects and cut the risk of flooding to homes, businesses and infrastructures;
•	Coordinated the development of guidelines, Operational and maintenance manuals, trainings manuals related to flood control and water storage management infrastructures;
•	Lead the review of technical studies/papers and preparation of flood control and water storage projects while safeguarding the environment, health, and safety and promoting inclusiveness.
•	Directed and supervised crew engaging in dredging operations in rivers, retention ponds and lakes across the country;
•	Developed dredging operation guidelines for rivers, lakes and detention ponds;
•	Verified depth of excavations to make sure that excavations are made according to requirements;

Successfully served as Site Engineer on the construction of Mark Cables FZE factory in Nyanza District. 

Key Responsibilities 
•	Managing overall construction project;
•	Developing Construction plans and overseeing building works; 
•	Supporting and manage the planning and Perform Constructability review over design stage of Construction projects;
•	Checking technical designs and drawings to ensure that they are followed correctly;
•	Responsible for overall coordination and supervision of contracted Staffs;
•	Ensuring projects packages meet agreed specifications, budget and/or timescales;
•	Liaising with clients, subcontractors and other professional staff, especially quantity surveyors and General Manager;
•	Providing technical advices and solving problem on site;
•	Reporting the project progress to the General Manager;
•	Liaising with quantity surveyors about ordering and pricing of materials;
•	Drafting Technical Support documents;

Outline
Under Water for Growth Rwanda, a four-year joint Rwanda-Netherlands initiative in implementing an integrated approach to water management, we had a mission to achieve three main goals: Equitable, efficient and environmentally sustainable water resources. 

Key Responsibilities
•	Conducted through Integrated Water Resource Management Programme (IWRM), a technical study on flood management in volcanoes areas (Nyabihu, Musanze and Rubavu) using hydraulic and hydrological models; as the output, five projects related to flood mitigation and catchment restoration (Volcano flood control project, Bukeri Diversion channel, Sebeya lateral dyke, New Muhazi Dyke, and Sebeya Dam) were developed and are currently being implemented by Rwanda Water Resources Board; 
•	Coordinated the development and management of water, land and related resources by assessing and monitoring surface water, groundwater, water quality and sediment for four demonstrated catchments; 24 groundwater monitoring stations were installed across the country and currently, data collected are being collected in different areas (Industrial and academia);  
•	Elaborated  a  participatory  mapping  of  issues,  opportunities  and  priority  interventions  of  the Catchment plans 2.0; therefore, intervention areas were identified and are currently being restored by the use of proposed natural based solutions.

Key responsibilities
•	Enhanced community resilience to waterborne and related diseases through WASH training programme in Gastibo, Nyagatare and Huye Districts;
•	Successfully conducted Hydro- geological investigations and Vertical Electrical Sounding for groundwater exploration in five districts of Rwanda;
•	Constructed 15 boreholes for supplying clean water in communities of Gatsibo, Kirehe, Huye and Nyagatare Districts;
•	Cross-checked VES and WASH reports from francophone countries: Togo, DRC, Cameroun, and Malawi and reported back to Director of Implementation at Water 4;
•	Technical evaluation on other projects by ensuring potential risks concerning water distribution system are addressed with an appropriate balance of technical and business requirements;
•	Carry out investigations and failure analysis to pinpoint the failure & develop suitable recommendations that will ensure optimum level of integrity.

Key Responsibilities
•	Review all structure, architecture and MEP drawings and coordinate with the consultant for clarification and where necessary issue a request for information (RFI) or request for Change (RFC); 
•	Preparation of daily and weekly reports;
•	Heading and coordinating the site team for conducting the execution of all construction works in line with construction drawings and specifications;
•	Following up and updating the project planning and scheduling;
•	Preparation of BBS and reinforcement take off quantities;
•	Ensuring the concrete cube test are taken and monitored until they are crushed and sharing the results with the consultants;
•	Maintain and monitoring all construction documents;
•	Assisting the QS during preparation of certificate and billing;
•	Preparation of shop drawings and submitting them for approval.
•	Co-ordination of all site related matters, with respect to sub-contractors;
•	Working with the project team during the preparation of provisional account and handover.
